The '''Battle of Jarte''' was fought from 4 to 16 April 1542 between the forces of Imam [[Ahmad ibn Ibrahim al-Ghazi]] and a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] expeditionary force fighting on behalf of the [[Ethiopian Empire]]. The Portuguese were led by [[Cristóvão da Gama]]. The Portuguese were victorious.

