{{Infobox UK school | name = Beaulieu Convent School | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | size = | alt = | caption = | image2 = | size2 = | alt2 = | caption2 = | motto = | motto_pl = | established = {{Start date|1951}} | approx = | closed = | c_approx = | type = [[Independent school]] | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | president = | head_label = | head = Mr C Beirne | r_head_label = | r_head = | deputy_head_label = | deputy_head = | r_deputy_head_label = | r_deputy_head = | chair_label = | chair = | founder = | founder_pl = | medium = | street = Wellington Road | locality = | city = [[Saint Helier|St Helier]] | postcode = JE2 4RJ | country = [[Jersey]] | urn = 132523 | staff = | capacity = | enrollment = <!-- {{As of|YYYY|MM|lc=on}} --> | gender = Girls (sixth-form mixed with other private schools for courses) | lower_age = 3 | upper_age = 18 | houses = | colours = Navy, dark blue, light blue | publication = | publication_pl = | free_label_1 = | free_1 = | free_label_2 = | free_2 = | free_label_3 = | free_3 = | coordinates = {{coord|49|11|18|N|2|5|41|W|type:edu_region:GB|display=title}} | pushpin_map = Channel Islands | website = http://www.beaulieu.jersey.sch.uk/ | website_name = School website | bodystyle = }}
'''Beaulieu Convent School''' is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[independent school]] for girls located in [[Saint Helier|St Helier]], [[Jersey]].
The school was established in 1951 by sisters from the [[Order of the Immaculate Conception]]. In 1999 the Order of the Immaculate Conception gifted Beaulieu School, the site and its buildings to the island of Jersey on the understanding it would remain a Catholic School.
Today the school is divided into preschool, [[Primary education|primary]] and [[Secondary education|secondary]] departments, and also operates a [[sixth form]]. Courses of study offered at the school include [[GCSE]]s, [[A Level]]s and [[Business and Technology Education Council|BTEC]]s.
