{{Infobox diocese | jurisdiction = Eparchy<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese --> | name = Adigrat | latin = Eparchia Adigratensis | local = <!-- Name in the native language --> | image = Cathedral of the Holy Saviour, Adigrat .jpg | image_size = 250px | image_alt = | caption = Cathedral of the Holy Saviour, Adigrat <!---- Locations ----> | country = {{flag|Ethiopia}} | territory = | province = [[Ethiopian Catholic Archeparchy of Addis Abeba|Addis Ababa]] | coordinates = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> <!---- Statistics ----> | area_km2 = 80,000<!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> | population = 4,601,000 | population_as_of = 2010 | catholics = 22,687<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese --> | catholics_percent = .5 | parishes = 36<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese --> | churches = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese --> | congregations = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese --> | schools = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese --> | members = <!-- Number of members in the diocese --> <!---- Information ----> | denomination = [[Ethiopian Catholic Church]] | rite = [[Alexandrian Rite]] | established = 25 March 1937 ({{age|1937|3|25}} years ago) | cathedral = [[Cathedral of the Holy Saviour, Adigrat|Cathedral of the Holy Saviour]] | cocathedral = | patron = | priests = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese --> <!---- Current leadership ----> | pope = {{Incumbent pope}} | bishop = [[Tesfasellassie Medhin]] | bishop_title = [[Bishop]] | coadjutor = | auxiliary_bishops = | vicar_general = | emeritus_bishops = <!---- Map ----> | map = Ethiopia - Eparchia di Adigrat.jpg | map_alt = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = | footnotes = }}
The '''Ethiopian Catholic Eparchy of Adigrat''' ({{lang-la|Eparchia Adigratensis}}) is a [[Ethiopian Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[eparchy]] located in the city of [[Adigrat]], [[Ethiopia]]. It is in the [[ecclesiastical province]] of [[Ethiopian Catholic Archeparchy of Addis Abeba|Addis Ababa]].
==History== On 25 March 1937, [[Pope Pius XI]] established the [[Apostolic prefect|Prefecture Apostolic]] of [[Tigray Region|Tigray]] from the [[Ethiopian Catholic Archeparchy of Addis Abeba|Vicariate Apostolic of Abyssinia]]. [[Pope John XXIII]] elevated it as the Eparchy of Adigrat on 20 February 1961.<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dadig.html|title=Eparchy of Adigrat (Ethiopian)|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref><ref name=gcatholic>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/adig0.htm|title=Ethiopic Diocese of Adigrat|publisher=GCatholic.org|accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref>
==OVC Project== {{main article|OVC project|Student Initiative Rahel}} The ADCS (''Adigrat Diocese Catholic Secretary'') is responsible for the disbursement of grants to [[scholarship]] holders of the diocese within the scope of the ''[[OVC project]]'' (OVC = "Orphans and Vulnerable Children"), funded by the [[Student Initiative Rahel]] of the ''Institute for World Church and Mission'' (IWM) (German: ''Institut für Weltkirche und Mission'') which is a part of the ''[[Sankt Georgen Graduate School of Philosophy and Theology]]'' in [[Sachsenhausen (Frankfurt am Main)|Frankfurt-Sachsenhausen]], [[Germany]] and passed by the ''[[Pontifical Mission Societies]]'' (German: ''missio''). The OVC-project has already supported ten young people with micro-scholarships for obtaining a university entrance qualification and at least one [[bachelor's degree]] in their own country. The Rahel project helps to support [[discrimination|disadvantaged]] [[youth|young people]] in the [[Tigray region]] as part of the [[Development aid|development cooperation]] through micro-scholarships and accompanies them during their studies or their training.<ref name="IWM-Rahel-Festschrift">{{cite journal| author1 = Judith Breunig | author2 = Madeleine Helbig | author3 = Claudia Berg | author4 = Stefanie Matulla | author5 = Magdalena Strauch | author6 = Marita Wagner | author7 = Benedikt Winkler | title = Rahel - Ein Bildungsprojekt für Adigrat - Festschrift der Studierendeninitiative – Ein Blick durch die Zeit: 2010–2015 (=Rahel - An education project for Adigrat - Festschrift of the initiative by students - A view through the years: 2010-2015) | publisher = Rahel-Bildungsprojekt (=Student Initiative Rahel) (SIR) / Institut für Weltkirche und Mission (=Institute for World Church and [[Christian mission|Mission]]) (IWM) | language = German | date = June 2015}}</ref> <ref name="IWM-Rahel-Webseite">{{cite web| url = http://www.iwm.sankt-georgen.de/rahel-bildungsprojekt/ | title = Rahel – Ein Bildungsprojekt für Adigrat (=Rahel - An educational project for Adigrat), official website | publisher = Rahel-Bildungsprojekt (=Student Initiative Rahel) (SIR) / Institut für Weltkirche und Mission (=Institute for World Church and Christian mission) (IWM) | language = German | accessdate = 12 December 2016}}</ref> Due to personnel fluctuation among students at the Sankt Georgen Graduate School of Philosophy and Theology, the project has been phasing out slowly since the end of 2017. The tasks of the support are gradually taken over by the ''Adigrat Diocesan Catholic Secretariat'' (ADCS) and former graduates in Ethiopia.<ref name="IWM-Rahel-Letter">{{cite web | url = https://iwm.sankt-georgen.de/file/Brief-an-Spender.pdf | title = Brief an Spender(=Letter to donors) | author = Rahel-Team | publisher = Rahel-Bildungsprojekt (=Student Initiative Rahel) (SIR) / Institut für Weltkirche und Mission (=Institute for World Church and Christian mission) (IWM) | format = PDF | language = German | date = 15 November 2017 | accessdate = 4 August 2018}}</ref>
